<p class="animated" data-animate="fadeInUp" data-delay=".16">Cookies Interlay does use technologies such as cookies. Cookies are small pieces of information or data that the website can send to your browser, which may then be stored on your computer&rsquo;s hard drive (persistent cookies) or its memory (session cookies). Cookies help Interlay understand which parts of our website are the most popular, where our visitors are going and how long they spend there. We use cookies to learn how we can make our website more useful and interesting for you. You may be able to adjust your browser settings to notify you when you receive a cookie, giving you the chance to decide whether or not to accept it.</p>

